<li id="cite_note-truth-35"><b><a href="#cite_ref-truth_35-0" title="">^</a></b> Peirce offered a sophisticated definition of truth in tandem with his definition of the real, as presuppositions of reason, all by way of example in his exposition of pragmatic logical method. See <a href="/wiki/Pragmaticism" title="Pragmaticism">Pragmaticism</a> and also the many passages by Peirce quoted under "Truth" and "Real, Reality" at the <i>Commens Dictionary of Peirce's Terms</i> (<a href="http://www.helsinki.fi/science/commens/dictionary.html" class="external text" title="http://www.helsinki.fi/science/commens/dictionary.html" rel="nofollow">Eprint</a>).</li>
