<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Charles_Sanders_Peirce&amp;action=edit&amp;section=32" title="Edit section: References">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">References</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-size:120%"><b>Works by C. S. Peirce</b></span></p>
<p><b>Papers and articles.</b> Links embedded in page numbers are to original editions via <i>Google Book Search</i>, users outside the USA may be unable to access. References to NEM may be missing because of unavailability of its table of contents. Some of these works have also been reprinted in collections besides the main editions.</p>
<ul>
<li>(1867), "<a href="http://en.wikisource.org/wiki/On_a_New_List_of_Categories" class="extiw" title="s:On a New List of Categories">On a New List of Categories</a>", <i>Proceedings of the American Academy of Arts and Sciences</i> v. 7 (1868), pp. <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=nG8UAAAAYAAJ&amp;jtp=287" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=nG8UAAAAYAAJ&amp;jtp=287" rel="nofollow">287</a>–298. Presented 14 May 1867. Reprinted CP 1.545–559, W 2, 49–59, EP (<a href="http://www.iupui.edu/~peirce/writings/v2/w2/w2_04/v2_4.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.iupui.edu/~peirce/writings/v2/w2/w2_04/v2_4.htm" rel="nofollow">PEP Eprint</a>), EP 1, 1–10. <a href="http://www.cspeirce.com/menu/library/bycsp/newlist/nl-frame.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.cspeirce.com/menu/library/bycsp/newlist/nl-frame.htm" rel="nofollow"><i>Arisbe</i> Eprint</a>.</li>
<li>(1868), "What Is Meant by 'Determined'", <i>Journal of Speculative Philosophy</i> v. 2, no. 3: <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=YHkqP2JHJ_IC&amp;pg=RA1-PA190" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=YHkqP2JHJ_IC&amp;pg=RA1-PA190" rel="nofollow">190</a>-91. Reprinted CP6.625-630. <a href="http://www.iupui.edu/~peirce/writings/v2/w2/w2_16/v2_16.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.iupui.edu/~peirce/writings/v2/w2/w2_16/v2_16.htm" rel="nofollow">PEP Eprint</a></li>
<li>(1877), "<a href="http://en.wikisource.org/wiki/The_Fixation_of_Belief" class="extiw" title="s:The Fixation of Belief">The Fixation of Belief</a>", <i>Popular Science Monthly</i> v. 12: 1–15. Reprinted CP 5.358-387, W 3, 242–257, EP 1, 109–123. <a href="http://www.peirce.org/writings/p107.html" class="external text" title="http://www.peirce.org/writings/p107.html" rel="nofollow"><i>Arisbe</i> Eprint</a>.</li>
<li>(1878), "<a href="http://en.wikisource.org/wiki/How_to_Make_Our_Ideas_Clear" class="extiw" title="s:How to Make Our Ideas Clear">How to Make Our Ideas Clear</a>", <i>Popular Science Monthly</i> v. 12: 286–302. Reprinted CP 5.388-410, W 3, 257–276), EP 1, 124–141. <a href="http://www.cspeirce.com/menu/library/bycsp/ideas/id-frame.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.cspeirce.com/menu/library/bycsp/ideas/id-frame.htm" rel="nofollow"><i>Arisbe</i> Eprint</a>.</li>
<li>(1878), "The Probability of Induction", <i>Popular Science Monthly</i> v. 12: 705-718. Reprinted CP 2.669-693, W 3, 290-305, EP 1, 155-169.</li>
<li>(1880), "A Boolean Algebra with One Constant", MS, CP 4.12-20.</li>
<li>(1881), "On the Logic of Number", <i>American Journal of Mathematics</i> v. 4: <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=LQgPAAAAIAAJ&amp;jtp=85" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=LQgPAAAAIAAJ&amp;jtp=85" rel="nofollow">85</a>-95. Reprinted CP 3.252-288, W 4, 299-309.</li>
<li>(1884-1885), "On the Algebra of Logic: A Contribution to the Philosophy of Notation", <i>American Journal of Mathematics</i> v. 7, two parts, first part published 1885, pp. <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=lwYPAAAAIAAJ&amp;&amp;pg=PA180" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=lwYPAAAAIAAJ&amp;&amp;pg=PA180" rel="nofollow">180</a>–202. Presented, National Academy of Sciences, Newport, RI, 14–17 Oct 1884. Reprinted CP 3.359–403, W 5, 162–190, EP 1, 225–228, in part.</li>
<li>(1899), "F.R.L." (First Rule of Logic), unpaginated manuscript. Reprinted CP 1.135–140. <a href="http://www.princeton.edu/~batke/peirce/frl_99.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.princeton.edu/~batke/peirce/frl_99.htm" rel="nofollow">Eprint</a>.</li>
<li>(1902), "Application of C.S. Peirce to the Executive Committee of the Carnegie Institution, July 15, 1902." Published in Eisele, Carolyn, ed. (1976) as "Parts of Carnegie Application (L75)" in <i>The New Elements of Mathematics by Charles S. Peirce</i>, v. 4, <i>Mathematical Philosophy</i>. The Hague, Netherlands: Mouton Publishers: 13–73. The complete submitted application plus drafts labeled and interpolated by Joseph Ransdell, ed., are online in "Logic, Regarded As Semeiotic (The Carnegie application of 1902)", (1998), <i>Arisbe</i> <a href="http://www.cspeirce.com/menu/library/bycsp/l75/l75.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.cspeirce.com/menu/library/bycsp/l75/l75.htm" rel="nofollow">Eprint</a>.</li>
<li>(1908), "<a href="http://en.wikisource.org/wiki/A_Neglected_Argument_for_the_Reality_of_God" class="extiw" title="s:A Neglected Argument for the Reality of God">A Neglected Argument for the Reality of God</a>", published in part, <i>Hibbert Journal</i> v. 7, 90-112. Reprinted with unpublished part CP 6.452-485, EP 2, 434-450. <a href="http://users.xplornet.com/~gnox/CSPgod.htm#na1" class="external text" title="http://users.xplornet.com/~gnox/CSPgod.htm#na1" rel="nofollow">Eprint</a>.</li>
</ul>
